<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/17973865-pear001">Pear001</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">1) I love this series. My favorite by far and I would always give it a ten but let&apos;s pretend I&apos;m not being biased and 9.9/10?<br/>2) there are four boys an<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">1) I love this series. My favorite by far and I would always give it a ten but let's pretend I'm not being biased and 9.9/10?<br />2) there are four boys and one girl. One boy had a brief crush on her and one who may be in love with her and she with him. There is also one boy with a HEAVILY implied crush on another boy. Romance is not as strong as you'd think it would be considering genre and the whole "kiss your true love and he dies" thing but when it does creep up its swoon worthy.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
